description:
&lt;p&gt;The Assertive Outreach Service is looking for an enthusiastic and experienced Clinical Psychologist to work across its two clinical teams. You would be working with a Consultant Clinical Psychologist to provide psychologically informed care directly and indirectly to people who have distressing unusual experiences across Leeds. The service is committed to moving towards a trauma informed clinical model and this post would contribute to the development of this approach. This post will suit anyone who has experience and/or a strong interest in working with people with a lived experience of psychosis and with complex presentations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An interest and the skills to support professional colleagues to develop and use psychological thinking in their work with service users will be a central component of the post. This would also include further training in either CBT or family therapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of and training in supervision will be important as the role involves provision of supervision to psychologists in training and other professionals within the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supervision for clinical work will be provided by staff with expertise and experience in the above areas of work. Interviews are planned to take place on 8th December 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Please note any correspondence following application will be sent via trac.jobs &amp; the Trust&#39;s Resourcing Team**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anjula Gupta, Consultant Clinical Psychologist/ Tom Hitchen – Louden, Clinical Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anjula - 0113 855 6240 (Monday, Tuesday or Thursday only))&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tom – 0113 855 7091&lt;/p&gt;
